		<div>Ok you asked for it so here it is 20 MINUTE timer every second there...<br />
<br />
NOTE when it changes from 9:59 to 10:00 the Seconds digit will apear a slight bit larger than the minute/10s of seconds digits since it shrinkes the 3 digit number slightly to fit in space..but you should see what ya wanna see, an accurate running timer in game...lol Testing this thing sucked sitting for 20 minutes making sure every number eapeared...and glad i did cause i listed the 5 minute 2 times lol<br />
<br />
i moved the Zip file to Beta Thread, use it abuse it, its alot of code about 120 Sets of frames, the .TGA file is quite large but easiest way to get it all where i needed it<br />
<br />
if you make your own timer, i suggest you look at how i laid out my TGA as it makes it very easy to Cut and Paste and only have to edit one Coordiante per Minute set, i broke down and seperated each set by the Minute so you can easily see where what is</div>
